{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|き}}
/ki<sub>2</sub>/: {{IPAchar|[kɨ]}} > {{IPAchar|[ki]}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|木|tr=ki<sub>2</sub>}} (cf. phonetic Man'yōgana form {{ltc-l|紀}}), from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*kəy}}. Cognate with {{cog|jpx-ryu-pro|*ke}}, whence {{cog|ams|けぃー|tr=kʰɨː}}, {{cog|ryu|きー|tr=kiː}}, {{cog|xug|きー|tr=kʰiː}}, {{cog|mvi|きー|tr=kiː}}, {{cog|rys|きー|tr=kiː}} and {{cog|yoi|きー|tr=kʰiː}}. Likely developed from fusion of older form ''*kə'' + {{m|ja|い|tr=i|pos=emphatic nominative particle}}, similar to the sound changes at work in {{m|ja|神}} in the shift from ''kamu'' to ''kami''.<ref name="Perard 2012">{{cite-web|first=Thomas|last=Pellard|title=日琉祖語の分岐年代
|work=琉球諸語と古代日本語に関する比較言語学的研究」ワークショップ|year=2012|url=http://kikigengo.jp/nishihara/lib/exe/fetch.php?media=library:references:rkoj-pellard.pdf|page=6}}</ref>

Now the modern {{etyl|ja|-}} word.

{{ja-noun|け}}

# a [[tree]]
#: {{ux|ja|麻都能'''氣'''乃 奈美多流美礼波 伊波妣等乃 和例乎美於久流等 多々理之母己呂|tr=松の'''木'''の 並みたる見れば 家人の 我れを見送ると 立たりしもころ<br
/>まつの'''け'''の なみたるみれば いはびとの われをみおくると たたりしもころ<br
/>''Matsu no '''ke''' no / namitaru mireba / iwabito no / ware o miokuru to / tatari shi mokoro''|t=Looking at the pine '''trees''' all in a row, they were just like the people from the household standing to see me off|ref=<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|20|4375}}; [http://etext.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man20Yo.html#4375 text here]</ref>}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|こ}}
/ko<sub>2</sub>/: {{IPAchar|[kə]}} > {{IPAchar|[ko̞]}} 

